news.title: China's Shimao Group share plunge adds to property woes
news.para: Shimao and its subsidiaries will need to refinance or repay $2.5 billion in bond maturities through 2022, according to Bloomberg data, with a 30 million yuan ($4.7 million) repayment due on Friday and a two billion yuan note due next month.

news.title: Karnataka may amend law to make land conversion easier to spur investments
news.para: The Karnataka Land Revenue Act, 1964, requires owners of farmland to apply for conversion to change the nature of the land from agriculture to non-agriculture. Later, the planning authorities will further classify them as residential, industrial, educational, commercial, etc.

news.title: Over 2,400 statutory towns have online building permission system: Government
news.para: ​In written reply to a question, Union Housing and Urban Affairs Minister Hardeep Singh Puri said his ministry is expediting the implementation of online building permission system in all statutory towns.

news.title: REPL appointed as consultant for completion of Unitech projects in Gurugram
news.para: The Supreme Court appointed board of Unitech group has appointed Delhi-based consultancy company REPL (Rudrabhishek Enterprises Ltd Project Management Consultants (PMC) for taking forward the assignments and ensuring timely delivery of homes to the homebuyers.

news.title: Noida authority now ready to install smart water meters after four-year delay
news.para: A total of 5,000 meters are slated to be installed in the first phase, under a pilot project that aims at ending water wastage and bringing more transparency in billings.

news.title: Pooja Dhoot buys luxury duplex in South Mumbai for Rs 52 crore
news.para: The project has witnessed several record-setting transactions in the last few months. In December, the Motilal Oswal family trust bought two duplex apartments spread over 6,800 sq ft on the 13th and 17th floors of the same high-rise building for Rs 101 crore.

news.title: Tamil Nadu can earn Rs 5,000 crore by accounting inter-state M-sand & blue metal trucks
news.para: In a press release on Monday, the federation said that about 700 overloaded trucks from Krishnagiri are carrying M-Sand and blue metal without transit passes, e-way bill and GST bills to Bengaluru on a daily basis.

news.title: Nagpur's Zqube Infracon seeks NCLT nod on Srei-run property auction
news.para: It was declared as the highest bidder for the commercial property in Powai, Mumbai after an e-auction was held on August 11 for the property.

news.title: Panel cites lack of clarity in proposed plan variations in Kovalam-Vizhinjam scheme
news.para: It has been cited that the changes could have been incorporated within the master plan, since the plan covers the areas originally included under the Kovalam-Vizhinjam area development scheme.

news.title: Adani Realty in advanced talks to buy Ozone Group at about $1 billion
news.para: Adani Realty Ltd. is seeking to take over the Bengaluru-based Ozone, which has an outstanding debt of more than 60 billion rupees ($790 million), one of the people said, asking not to be named as the information is not public.

news.title: Regularise old illegal colonies: Gurugram MP
news.para: “Demolition of such colonies has left several families homeless and the state government should regularise these colonies where several families have been residing for years,” Rao Inderjit said.

news.title: Pune: 50% property tax pending in Dehu Road Cantonment
news.para: About Rs3.7 crore worth of tax is pending and the cantonment has sent notices to the defaulters in the last few months.

news.title: Nashik: Only online building plan submissions from January 1
news.para: The builders will have to submit building plans online from January 1. The offline submission and approval of building plans had been started around three to four months ago following some problems with the online software.

news.title: Gurugram corporation to target big property tax defaulters
news.para: The zonal taxation officers have been directed to first identify property tax defaulters with dues over Rs 1 lakh and recover the same from them.

news.title: Government to ease building laws: Tamil Nadu CM
news.para: The state government will roll out deemed approvals for planning permission applications based on self-attestation. It will also launch a single-window system to facilitate planning permission for layouts and housing plots within 60 days.
